{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0cd67477-416d-415f-bb0f-6dcfe70bfe48","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n   > **Note:** This requires upgrading to **xUnit.net v3** — MTP is not supported on xUnit v2.x.\n\n3. **Upgrade your test packages** from `xunit` (v2) to `xunit.v3`:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n4. **Update your code** for xUnit v3 breaking changes (namespaces, API changes, etc.).\n\n5. **Enable MTP** in your project file (if not auto-enabled):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n6. Run tests with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained).\n\n**Key point:** xUnit v2.x only supports VSTest. To use Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you **must** migrate to xUnit v3, which is a more significant change than just swapping a runner package. Review the [xUnit v3 migration guide](https://xunit.net/docs/getting-started/v3/migration) for full details on API changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79c98936-7b84-44b0-b248-83757b72ba3d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"703A:1CDC41:E023D67:F64F093:69F2A766"},"id":"8a4ee57d-0c96-4e21-a6f7-b7583698f210","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:50:56.127Z","parentId":"c9c47b1c-480d-41c5-b2f3-f34ec46aa28c"}
